# Normalize line endings. Text files are checked out as LF on every platform so
# JVM source-position macros (e.g. Kyo's `Frame` / kyo-test `assert`) don't
# miscount offsets on CRLF and crash with StringIndexOutOfBoundsException.
# Keeping batch files LF as well avoids dirty working copies in colocated JJ
# repos, where CRLF checkout filters are surfaced as raw file changes.
# Without this, GitHub's Windows runners (core.autocrlf=true) can check out CRLF
# and the test compile fails. See getkyo/kyo#1678 thread / Eleven19/kymora#3.
* text=auto eol=lf
